{"page":16,"prev_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1429517/reasons?page=15&page_size=500","next_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1429517/reasons?page_size=500","total_pages":9,"reasons":[]}{"page":7,"prev_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1429517/reasons?page=6&page_size=500","next_page_endpoint":"http://api.change.org/v1/petitions/1429517/reasons?page=8&page_size=500","total_pages":9,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:01:03Z","content":"amanda noud","like_count":0,"author_name":"amanda noud","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70108555"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:22:06Z","content":"I too am a mother.  Enough said.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christy Saunby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66605912"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:15:41Z","content":"It concerns me for anyone who gets injured in Cuba..do the physicians/hospitals just want the money involved? ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Connie Borgel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77846420"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:00:21Z","content":"D. Andrew White","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Andrew White","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60678734"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:08:36Z","content":"If no crime is charged this woman deserves her freedom and a chance to start a grieving process (if such a thing is even possible)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Justin Lakes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78896391"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:48:35Z","content":"No parent should have to suffer the loss of their child and then be purposely held from not attending their funeral. She is already suffering from the lost of her son and now, not being able to say goodbye... Not acceptable!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy Hardee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78901433"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:55:31Z","content":"If it were me and knowing it was not at fault and no charges pending for wrongful actions. There is no reason to detain her.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patrcia Lindsay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72335677"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:06:00Z","content":"Please free her. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lynn Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78914109"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:48:35Z","content":"i believe she should be brought back to canada , but not for closure ...\r\naltho it is entirely her fault her \r\nchild was on that scooter \r\nAnd her responsibility \r\n\r\ni sign this because i think she \r\nshould be prosecuted in canada for neglect and manslaughter \r\n\r\nhonestly what kind of mother \r\nwould put her child on a scooter\r\nperiod , let alone in such a \r\ndangerous place \r\n\r\ncanada has chosen not to help \r\nbecause they see this as helping a murder \r\n\r\ni see it as making her face what \r\nshe has done and live with \r\nthat the rest of her life .\r\n\r\nit sounds horrible to say \r\nbut has anybody though of the \r\nchild ?he will never live a full \r\nlife because his mom didnt \r\nlove him enough to rent a car .","like_count":0,"author_name":"billy mitton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45949975"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:53:02Z","content":"Although I was never fortunate enough to meet Justine or her son, Cameron, I have been told by people close to me that she is a loving and devoted mother and friend. Please help her come back in time for her son's funeral","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lisa Klingel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/63622189"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:12:20Z","content":"Because I am a mother. There would be nothing more important than to be there for the funeral of my son. I couldn't imagine not being able to say goodbye. We need to take care of our own and bring this Canadian mother home to her son.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Roy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30334685"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:29:33Z","content":"It's the right thing. Every mother deserves the opportunity to properly grieve a loss of a child","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78867598"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T19:22:28Z","content":"I don't think it's right to detain Justine!She is Cameron's mother,she needs to be there!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Della  M. Broder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69377851"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:21:03Z","content":"what a sad tragic story.  Why are they not letting her fly out?  it's shameful ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Abigail Jacob","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20939573"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:06:51Z","content":"Because I believe that Justine has a right to leave Cuba and come back her home land Canada and go to her child funeral.  Canada and the embassy should take part and do their part in helping this girl get home on time.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leandro Abrantes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78871887"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T23:19:37Z","content":"Justine needs to be home with her family to help her grieve the loss of her beautiful son.   No child should be buried without their parents being part of the goodbye ceremony. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Roxane Nicholson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78782369"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:26:47Z","content":"how terrible to be held in the country where your son died and not be able to bury him in your country with your family.  let her go!  why are you holding her.  Please!!!! as a mom and as a decent person who knows the right thing to do in the face of tragedy to say goodbye and have closure, I appeal to you.","like_count":0,"author_name":"jane truemner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21097655"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:01:55Z","content":"Let this girl come home to bury her child.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janice MacGillivary","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16754590"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:07:13Z","content":"It's important to me because I believe in human rights, human equity, and moral values. If there is NO good reason for this women to be held in Cuba then bring her home. Perhaps contacting Human Rights Watch, Amensty international, the UN, Oxfam, etc may help ?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Noelle Hajjar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1960725"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:31:11Z","content":"What a heartbreaking situation. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"yvonne chamberlin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/49788073"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:33:53Z","content":"Please, for the sake of common decency, allow Justine Davis home for her son's funeral !!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robert Gardner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78892750"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:36:55Z","content":"She has every right to leave!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jackie Dawe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78893047"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:49:39Z","content":"she needs to be with her family during this time!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"janet rivera","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78894284"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:52:34Z","content":"Justine is a Canadian who has suffered a terrible tragedy. We as  her country have to be there for her. You as our Gov. rep have to do you job and get her home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Barbara Cullen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58344065"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:34:33Z","content":"It's the right thing to do. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ulf Teschendorff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47101540"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:01:34Z","content":"This is outrageous. Help this poor woman","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy Wright","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64146239"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:28:02Z","content":"I want this mother to see her child laid to rest. If she doesn't, it'll hurt her more than the fact that the child is dead.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex Peterson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54505924"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:51:15Z","content":"That is a Canadian down there in Cuba! Why is our government NOT doing everything possible to get her home? Contact via \"notes\"?!!! Are you kidding me? This child will only be put at rest once! Let's not allow this poor mother to miss this... And suffer another tragic this in her life!! We Are Canadian for Christ-sake! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Don Ellis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35701305"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T10:24:59Z","content":"Justine has a right to be home here in Canada to attend her sons funeral!  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Debra DiBattista","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78831352"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:38:17Z","content":"It is only proper that Justine has the opportunity to say a loving goodbye to her child.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marilyn Brimacombe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54291647"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:01:53Z","content":"Anyone deserves to be at the funeral of the tragic death of their own child. Particularly because she has not been charged with anything. If she was charged with the responsibility of this death, namely if she was intoxicated or driving unsafely with her child in the vehicle, this may be a different debate. Justine has not been charged with anything. Let them continue their investigation all they want, she should be released to attend the funeral and apprehended should they decide to charge her where she can then defend herself.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sharon Singer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78741885"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T21:57:15Z","content":"every mother has the right to say their final goodbyes no matter what the situation","like_count":0,"author_name":"carla hickmott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78749735"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:20:46Z","content":"I'm going on holidays myself with my son to the Dominican Republic and would hope the Canadian Government would be there for us if the need should arise!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Glenn Gardiner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71918488"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:57:14Z","content":"She is a fellow torontonian, and I feel soo sorry for her I can't imagine what she is feeling, stop the politics an let her home","like_count":0,"author_name":"nolan isenberg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14417997"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:00:22Z","content":"Estimados Cubanos, envia la chica a su pais para interrar su hijo, por respecto mutua.","like_count":0,"author_name":"isabel thomas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32490187"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T04:46:09Z","content":"As a mother, I would someone to fight for me and my freedom if I were in this situation. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jasmine Bourret","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/41996346"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T02:15:50Z","content":"One of the reasons that I am proud to pay taxes as a Canadian is that I thought our government would be there for us if you are ever in a situaiton like Justine Davis. I am deeply saddened and offended to read about this and realize that this is not the case. No mother should ever have to miss her son's funeral especially when she has done nothing wrong. Please let Justine Davis come home so she can say goodbye to her son. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bronwyn Addico","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32223100"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:36:56Z","content":"Bring her back to Canada!","like_count":0,"author_name":"shayan mehdi","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12430707"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:22:05Z","content":"I travel to Cuba often, and it's a shame to see the Cuban government not allowing a Canadian Citizen to go home to bury her child that should never be buried in the first place due to a tragic accident! It is a shame that Canadians support Cuba by travelling there and keeping their economy going. Please let Justine go home in time for her son's funeral!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Colleen Stevens","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78803092"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:13:57Z","content":"it should be obvious","like_count":0,"author_name":"priscilla duncan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22004952"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:19:16Z","content":"Thank GOD she is being released!!!!  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"James Ferland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78440037"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:34:33Z","content":"OMG you have to ask...i have compassion! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"phil welton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78899375"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:59:12Z","content":"BECAUSE I ALSO LOST A SON TO A DRUNKEN DRIVER AND SHE NEED'S TO BE WITH HER SON !! I JUST HOPE THIS HELP'S TO GET HER HOME!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"MARY MOORE","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78903145"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:30:07Z","content":"I have 2 sons myself and I couldnt imagine losing either of them , as mom I think its only right she should be able to say her final goodbye to her baby boy!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tiffany Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13525441"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:48:48Z","content":"I am a single father of a 17 year old daughter and if anything were to ever happen to her I would be devistated. To not allow this mother to be there to lay her poor dear son to rest is not only immoral but should be a crime in itself. It is disgusting that the Canadian government is not personally escourting her home. I am sure that if the members can fly around first class and in private jets on our taxpayer dime they sure as heck can arange to bring her home, regardless of what the Cuban gov has to say about it. How about Canadians stop going to Cuba for a few months?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan Pare","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55624438"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:19:55Z","content":"because i have kids, and feel just awful for the mom.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelly DeBruyn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78916779"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:26:02Z","content":"Its for a mother as a mother what I can do.","like_count":0,"author_name":"asima majeed","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/63879632"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T13:47:10Z","content":" No mother should ever have to bury their child and if something ever so horrible would happen a mother deserves to be there to lay him rest:(","like_count":0,"author_name":"justine morin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78851320"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:09:09Z","content":"Can't imagine the grief of losing a child and on top of that not being allowed to attend the funeral.  Beyond cruel and inhumane.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen  Houston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25301459"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:57:12Z","content":"I need to be able to trust my government when I travel. The performance of this government is deplorable. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bruce Ritchie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9465428"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:01:27Z","content":"Having Vacationed in beautiful Cayo Largo I do understand that Justine would have had to negotiate around the potholes and being a somewhat secluded place one would not expect an industrial sized truck to pop up, so I would implore you please help to get Justine Home. Regards  Michael J Byrne.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mike J Byrne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37143049"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:15:01Z","content":"It is unjust ","like_count":0,"author_name":"andrew valade","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78866970"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:39:15Z","content":"Cuban government behaviour will deter the tourism that is essential to many Cubans.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brian Atkinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62077135"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T23:46:22Z","content":"she deserves to attend her son's funeral....dont take away her chance to say goodbye to her child","like_count":0,"author_name":"Candace Cousins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6172231"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:33:56Z","content":"It's bad enough that her son has died, but not to be there for his funeral is absurd.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tammie Neumiller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66285304"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:43:35Z","content":"why do we have to make something so simple be so complicated - these are people's feelings involved - let's get it right!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Grace Poppy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65705915"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:28:37Z","content":"We feel that this poor mother has gone through enough but the thought that she can not say farewell to her only son is totally wrong and hope it will change for her our heart goes out to her Linda Wolf","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda  Wolf","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27001866"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T05:43:49Z","content":"This Girl Need to come home in Canada ....","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rachelle Desroches","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78812922"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:21:59Z","content":"No person should be deprived of being able to bury a loved one.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tristan Bairos","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53777806"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T13:12:49Z","content":"The Government should not stand for this type of behavior and should send the appropriate response down to Cuba to bring her back by whatever means nescessary ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeremy Osmond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16882382"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T13:04:52Z","content":"This woman has suffered enough already.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gayle Perryman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16853861"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:09:09Z","content":"After going through such an ordeal for Justine.  It is important that she join her family in Canada for her son's funeral.\r\nTherefore the least the Govt. can do is the have the mother attend her son's last respects.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Salman Jan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78853968"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:33:02Z","content":"the mother is experiencing the worst nightmare possible.  you need help!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nathalie Boivin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11994766"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:29:39Z","content":"The Canadian government needs to help Canadians abroad, which they don't. They think \" why were you outside of Canada\"  or \"what are you doing abroad\" worst record of any country when it comes to helping its own people overseas.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karl Darrall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44458104"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:44:10Z","content":"I have close friends who live in Cuba married to Cubans and would want to see Canada maintain open working relations especially in these trying circumstances.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dwayne Lowdermilk","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69575266"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:22:41Z","content":"Great cause!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Demian Borba","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78762018"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T22:55:03Z","content":"This is important because Justine should be allowed to leave Cuba.  Is it not enough that she has lost her son??\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Doris Pollock","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77460979"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:23:39Z","content":"It hurts enough to lose a child but it's cruelty beyond belief to make her miss her baby's funeral....have a heart for pities sake!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anita Clamp","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78278190"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:36:57Z","content":"It is important to me because I am a mother and no mother should have to go through something like this. She is mourning her child and she won't even be able to say goodbye.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Claudette Barclay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43821356"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:03:33Z","content":"Nobody would want something like that to happen to them. If the story is correct as it is written, then it was clearly an accident. I don't blame her for wanting to go home. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michellle Frankhouser","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78895758"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:08:38Z","content":"There is no need to detain this individual, it was a trajic accident let her grieve.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Thea Buell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78896396"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:11:21Z","content":"Losing a child would be the hardest thing in the world to deal with and not having the closure you need would impact you the rest of your life.  I'd want someone to help me if I were in the same position. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Russell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78896728"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:23:27Z","content":"Release Justine !","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Spruth","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38809122"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:31:48Z","content":"I think it is horrible enough that this young mother loses her precious son, then, for the Cuba govt. detaining her.  How much hardship must she bear.  My heart is broken over this issue.  I pray they will allow her to leave Cuba, so that she may bury her son.\r\nI pray that god watches over her and her family.","like_count":0,"author_name":"FRANCINE SWIFT","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16358804"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:48:37Z","content":"I am also a mother, let her have closure and mourn in peace!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Murillo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11035204"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:50:35Z","conte