by properly and in the comfort of her family and frirneds!!!! I will keep Justine in my prayers!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kyletia Quick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78791371"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:59:14Z","content":"There are no charges - let her go home!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen Dust","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78903151"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:19:09Z","content":"IT NOT IMOROTANT TO ME, IT JUST SEEMS LIKE THE RIGHT THING TO DO, THIS LADY SHOULD GET BE ABLE TO MORN HER SON, THIS WAS AN UNFORNTUNED ACCIDENT. LET THE WOMEN GO HOME.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amy Barlow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12693591"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:21:25Z","content":"It is important to me because Justine, whom you can tell from the photos, clearly loved her son, and is beside herself with grief and needs to go home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Victor Lopez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1849309"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:23:40Z","content":"I Love Cuba. Have been many many times.  Cuba and Canada have what I believe to be good relations.  Communication is the key. It appears no one but the baby (and his mother) were hurt.  If it is a concern she may being a law suit then why can she not sign a waiver if she believes this is a true accident with the truck drivers not being at fault so that she can leave.  I feel for her loss.  Let's keep Cuba a desired designation for Canadians.  It's great for their economy and ours as well as one of the most beautiful island I have ever been to.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leslie Fallaise","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30367733"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:26:05Z","content":"what Mother could not relate to her pain and sign to help her be there to say her final goodbye's","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leanne Roach","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59291313"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:55:35Z","content":"It is not good  for