ote","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44392682"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:21:44Z","content":"No mother should miss her son's funeral if that is part of their belief.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sherrill Wright","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32348351"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:19:18Z","content":"our government is in it for the money not compassion dignity or respect.straight cash I feel our government has let the people of Canada down too many times.bring yves home","like_count":0,"author_name":"randy clark","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36472144"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:39:38Z","content":"Countries like Cuba will not respect her and they have a different judicial system","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jean-luk Larose","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58690700"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:02:01Z","content":"Please assist Justine Davis to get back home to Canada to say farewell to her little son. A very tragic story. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Willson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32868430"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:06:04Z","content":"It is very important to cause if I were in her shoes right now I would want to come home to say goodbye to my son.  It was an accidental death - horrible one - but this should not have an jurisdication as to why she is kept there against her will.  she did nothing wrong - why will they not let her go does not make any sense whatsoever\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"gloria wasylyniuk","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56328575"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:30:21Z","content":"According to the details, mother should be present at the funeral of her child...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Hagop Boulgarian","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42202752"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T13:52:42Z","content":"Any mother that has to go through the dreaded experience of losing a child should have the right to see her child laid to rest.  PLEASE LET HER COME HOME!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kim Hills","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78709108"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T14:27:26Z","content":"What has humanity and compassion been lost to?  This young mother, from what I understand, is already grieving too many losses and now she has to deal with the likes of the Cuban government and a Canadian Embassy who seems not to be doing what they should be doing.  PTSD is alive and kicking and she will be a huge victim (she already is) if she can't bury her son.  I have children, and god-children, and cousins and nieces and nephews and I can't possibly imagine how much torture this is and what she is going through.  I only know nobody seems to want to help her.  She is a victim not a criminal!","like_count":0,"author_name":"R K","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36769306"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T13:44:04Z","content":"This mother needs to be at her son's funeral. And back in her own country to begin the healing process.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sheila Murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47074828"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:57:20Z","content":"I'm a mother with a three year old and were it me i would want to be there.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Zamina Khan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78858767"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:19:47Z","content":"I just came back from Cuba in October after travelling with my 1 year old son and this is heartbreaking. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Krabbe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56120387"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:56:18Z","content":"Yes I find this very unusual. Cayo Largo is an isolated island, but they were brought to Havana. Also when you pass away (die) in any foreign country, it does cost alot to transport the deceased person back. I am assuming Justine needs special medical transportation to get back to Canada. When you travel to Cuba you are supposed to have travellers medical insurance to cover these things. All things said, in this situation, the Canadian Embassy should be able to get some answers for the family, so I would like to petition them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Montour","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26016024"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:40:10Z","content":"Seems a bit excessive. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ricky Christie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26574586"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:12:56Z","content":"Give Justine a chance to be at her son's funeral!","like_count":0,"author_name":"jan radford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27491982"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:19:04Z","content":"Its the only right option that exists in this situation. Pressure must be applied to allow her to come home. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christopher Brun","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/41349064"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:25:50Z","content":"This is disgraceful behavior by the Canadian Government. Actually, it is anti-Canadian. The government needs to act now to bring this young mother home to bury her child. She is not a criminal and if so, even criminals have rights. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tracey Wade","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27081521"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:09:41Z","content":"I will be making a visit to cuba shortly in the next month and I would like to know that their policies towrads canandians is not a strict one..this was an accident and nothing more and needs to be treated and let go to return home to family","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patricia Haram","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62327129"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:05:09Z","content":"No government can detain a Canadian citizen.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Luic Andre Mandeville","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45587729"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:39:57Z","content":"Justine Davis deserves the basic consular services and government support any Canadian is entitled to, but especially in this tragic circumstance.","like_count":0,"author_nam