ment can do something to help.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anne Henderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13405393"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:41:48Z","content":"if it was me i'd wanna be there too!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nadine Plante","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47584117"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:08:53Z","content":"No parent should have to bury their own child let alone not be able to attend.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tina Whitelaw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7900317"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:03:10Z","content":"It is a very tragic story and I am a mom and I cannot imagine what Justine is going through.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Claire Drecun","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78786393"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:53:39Z","content":"Jesus Love you\nTrust in The Lord","like_count":0,"author_name":"Grajaled Felipe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78888851"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:25:53Z","content":"Unfortunately, this is so typical of our government when it comes to Canadians in need out of the country","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bob Stripe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42680173"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:48:24Z","content":"She has lost both her father and her son.  Nightmare enough without being denied the right to attend the boy's funeral. She will have to live with this knowledge the rest of her life. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margaret Bergshoeff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7152426"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:06:18Z","content":"A mother and her child, separated for his funeral, though the mother not charged with responsibility for the accident? Where is the compassion on the Canadian or the Cuban side? Sounds like a very scary place to visit and run into difficulties!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Patricia Anne Elford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38081939"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:08:21Z","content":"free her so that she can say h