r government should help this mother for her to be there for her son's funeral.  Canada gov. should be ahame to treat our people like that.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Suzette Gratton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/61021589"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:16:14Z","content":"This tragedy should not be further compounded","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terri Hodges","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15770076"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:55:18Z","content":"Because I am a mother who lost a child","like_count":0,"author_name":"linda mchone","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78894877"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:58:17Z","content":"As a parent I could not imagine losing a child, but then to be detained in a country for is a bit crazy especially if she has not been charged with anything. I hope that the gov't will do its part to help Justine get back home where she needs to be. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anna Francis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78895180"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:34:32Z","content":"It was a tragic accident, why make her suffer anymore","like_count":0,"author_name":"sherry foland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78899370"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:59:11Z","content":"The mother needs to be at her son's funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Myrna Forge","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11038705"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:14:53Z","content":"Because one day one never knows when one could be in the same situation","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paul Du Mesnil","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29366162"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T13:12:44Z","content":"BEcause she should be home to bury her baby boy. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78705456"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:33:51Z","content":"Because I am a mother too. She should be able to bury her baby. No matter how they make it happen, they must make it happen!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sand