-06T18:15:20Z","content":"because it's the right thing to do","like_count":0,"author_name":"linda sabourin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47138116"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:48:57Z","content":"There is no wrong doing on her part.  I'm sure she was trying to prevent an accident, not cause one. Unfortunately that was not the case.  Let her go home to be with her son.   ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda White","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16288046"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:49:59Z","content":"I'm a father and definitely would not want to go through his as a parent. Especially after losing a child.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Frank Rod","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78901669"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:33:49Z","content":"Because I'm a mother ... ...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gulshan Valli","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35564473"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:39:54Z","content":"This is important to me because I am a mother and a grandmother, and most importantly I am a human being. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margaret Fast","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31910481"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:32:10Z","content":"I would feel it necessary to be at my own child's funeral to say a last goodbye.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lynda Clelland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40715193"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:09:07Z","content":"she needs to be at her childs funeral","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda MacIntyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46999848"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:48:36Z","content":"I like to think we are more compassionate then to deny a mother to lay her child to rest!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donna Nault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78862814"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:12:58Z","content":"This situation is an outrage!\r\nI couldn't imagine having to lay one of my children to rest, and the fact that this mother can't even say her final good-bye is outrageo