s. It is the worst possible thing to have a child decease prior to you but than to be robbed of her chance to say goodbye is not acceptable. Our government has power and it should be used for the good of all Canadian citizen's in times of crisis for those in need of aid. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle Dutcher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42529055"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:33:53Z","content":"The Canadian government has an obligation to Canadian citizens in other countries who are undergoing difficulties and need help. I cannot accept that they do not have contacts to enable them to help Justine Davis. Why do they have to have considerable pressure applied before they really move hard?\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Audrey  Coutts","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20594137"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:43:56Z","content":"For obvious reasons","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Irwin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77652008"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:51:23Z","content":"I feel she has a right to properly grieve her son","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leeann Peddle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78858307"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:00:40Z","content":"These kind of cases should take priority on top af all other \"political\" issues. It's is a matter of principle, empathy, ethics and logic.\r\n>>Estimado se\u00f1or Julio Garmendia Pe\u00f1a (CAN Cuban Ambassador), si tiene un corazon, por favor utiliselo para tratar de entender lo que esta pobre madre esta sufriendo en este momento. El desafortunado accidente ya se llevo un angelito al cielo, y la vida de esta mama esta arruinada para siempre. POR FAVOR HAGA LO IMPOSIBLE para que esta pobre madre pueda despedir su angelito por ultima vez. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gabriela Soubie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75789425"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:23:52Z","content":"The government needs to help Justine.  Cuba should be avoided if they treat tourists this way.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen Ward","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70334611"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:56:57Z","content":"I am a mother of three and my heart goes out to Justine.  No mother should have to fight for the right to lay her child to rest !","like_count":0,"author_name":"Francoise Gervais","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78749903"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:08:17Z","content":"Justine needs the love and support of her family and friends to heal.  There is no justifiable reason to keep her in Cuba.  Being at her sons funeral is also important to her recovery and to the grieving process.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wanda Zayachkowski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78154268"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T19:44:21Z","content":"We rented scooters on this very island, and have very fond memories of our trip.  So sad to hear of this trip having such tragedy.  We should be able to rely on our Embassy in situations like this, and it is sad to hear this Mom is still there with no support.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janette Whitmore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78756657"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:59:00Z","content":"This young woman clearly needs the support of her government and all the resources it can muster on her behalf. Her situation is tragic and must not be ignored.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jill Irwin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34400700"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:17:44Z","content":"Our government needs to stand up and get her home for the funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wendy Ranger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47337942"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:24:08Z","content":"Hasn't she suffered enough?  To lose the most precious gift this life has given her and now this?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandra Mirabal","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10804105"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:10:34Z","content":"Compassion for humanity.\r\nBe part of the solution.","like_count":0,"author_name":"EROCA ZEVIAR","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43812761"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:38:10Z","content":"This could happen to anyone.  It's not right that Justine is being held in Cuba and where is our elusive Canadian Government?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pete Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78464016"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:23:03Z","content":"as this is a terrible situation - it's just awful to make it even worse....my thoughts are with you all...especially Mama. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leanne Scott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50516356"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:29:10Z","content":"We were in Cayo Santa Maria Dec.  21-28 and were not aware of this horrible tragedy. Where is our government and why has the embassy not done more to get this mother out of Cuba. If this is how Canadians are treated, I won't visit Cuba ever again.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janet Cote","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70183616"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:12:29Z","content":"Losing a kid is hard enough.  She should at least get a chance to see him before he is put to rest.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Varinder Kainth","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52572139"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:25:33Z","content":"I am a mother myself & I cannot imagine the kind of pain this mother is having to deal with. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kassandra  Morris","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6207525"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:58:46Z","content":"Canadians need ago have the security and legal counsel available to them when unexpected events come yo the gore while travelling abroad. The horrific events, in & of hem selves, as described in the article should have captured and enabled our gavernment's attention and action long before this. Are CanadiAns not safe while travelling abroad? Aw seven help us if our government has zero credibility via diplomatic channels.  A mother has the right to attend her son's funeral, regardless of red tape or bureaucratic B.S. Disgraceful...indeed!","like_count":0,"author_name":"sam wingfield","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57490249"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:50:44Z","content":"She needs to be with her family in her time of need and she needs to say her final goodby to her little baby.... ","like_count":0,"author_name":"CARMEN ESCOBAR","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78911252"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:55:00Z","content":"It's not right that the Cuban government detain Justine since no one else was injured except her and Cameron.  I don't understand why she shouldn't be allowed to come home to bury her son...this is so sad, as this will be the last time and opportunity to see her son.  I can't imagine being in her shoes, and the Canadian government should act PROMPTLY to have her see her deceased son.  Let us also pray that God will move the concerned authorities' hearts and allow Justine to come home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shirley Gorospe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69830629"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:09:23Z","content":"The death of your child is probably one of the most traumatic experiences one can face--especially for the mother.   Not being there at the funeral will greatly impede her ability to have any sort of closure and peace with a high potential to mar the mother for life!  It's bad enough to lose your child, but to be refused to be allowed to go the funeral is insult to injury and unconscionable!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gregory Seaborn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74606801"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:14:15Z","content":"we are canadians and need to support each other!!!! Bring this woman home to her child's funeral!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"vesna pavlovic","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78860281"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:48:49Z","content":"wheres compassion its not in cuba ... so sad.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"da