,"author_name":"Jackie Ryan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78756461"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:11:49Z","content":"What the F*** is wrong with humanity.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Martin Latreille","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12134415"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:47:53Z","content":"I really don' think this","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda MacRae","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24264857"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:08:21Z","content":"If our ambassador is not in the country to help Canadians there why are you there? Only interested in the lucrative contracts you can assist Canadian businesses in getting? I am guessing. Help get this lady home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wayne Dinzey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48245475"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T22:04:47Z","content":"Let this grieving mother leave. How ridiculous!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Trish Bartlett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66914054"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:01:08Z","content":"Just because she was in a car accident does not mean she is guilty of anything.  As a mother... I know what I would feel like if I could not be there for MY child.... ESPECIALLY FOR THERE FUNERAL....","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brenda Nadjiwon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78801396"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:52:01Z","content":"Pictures don't lie, and you can see clearly that Justine was a devoted mom, and this is comign from another devoted mom, and I don't know what I would do if the final hour I had left to stand by their side was taken away from me. She needs this because there is never closure, but at least she can have something to hold onto instead of just memories of missing the chance to finalize her goodbyes.  I hate the way the world has made political opinions our way of life.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Palmer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16743202"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:54:58Z","content":"If this horrible accident was not her faught then she needs to be realeased to return home to bury her child. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Aracelis Shelly Mazur","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68276012"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:56:31Z","content":"canadian embassy officials are paid large salaries to look aftetr canadians they need to do their jobs","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Jellett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76373550"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:58:52Z","content":"The woman's son has died in an accident.  Surely she is suffering enough without adding to her grief and anxiety.","like_count":0,"author_name":"karen Bach","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3357647"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:06:07Z","content":"mother should be there to say good bye to her son ","like_count":0,"author_name":"derek  prince","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27101567"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:08:12Z","content":"She needs to say good bye to her son...put yourself in her shoes. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rose S.","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52179693"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:10:21Z","content":"That is so very sad and totally unacceptable.\r\nI am so sorry for your loss and I hope you get to come back home soon.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Isabelle Cossette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34576621"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:16:48Z","content":"It was an accident, My daughter was killed two years ago she was 33 years old a truck was speeding ran off the side of rd. she left behind twins\r\ntwo years old! A parent never stops suffering when a child dies. I've always wanted to visit \r\nCuba Been to Cozumel many times and Cancun other places.\r\nI think of Cuba often, don't do this to this poor lady she will never stop suffering!! NEVER\r\nPLEASE LET THIS LADY GO TO HER DEAD BABY ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angela Sutton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78905689"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:46:18Z","content":"I work in the funeral industry and deal with grieving families on a daily basis. I could not even start to imagine what her mental state of mind in there in Cuba while she is being detained. My prayer is that she can return home and lay her son to rest and be with her family as she grieves the loss of her son. May God comfort & give her strength in this time. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jody Jordan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78910484"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:55:12Z","content":"the situation is tragic enough and she should be allowed to leave Cuba to bury her beloved child","like_count":0,"author_name":"Barbara Warden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35315450"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:17:38Z","content":"Bring Justine home !","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joanne Bilodeau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56185724"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:42:17Z","content":"A mother should have the right to attend her own sons funeral!! How heartless can some people be???","like_count":0,"author_name":"Angela Gagne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62331504"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:09:33Z","content":"I am a mother of a little girl and what happened to this mother and her child was tragic. But to have to go through this injustice and turmoil and miss your own child's funeral- is unimaginable. If it were you, wouldn't you pray for a miracle and humanity to step in and help? Let's make this happen.","like_count":0,"author_name":"merry Baguio","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65179088"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:38:45Z","content":"No mother should not be there for her son's funeral. Diplomacy aside, if this was a Cuban citizen in Canada, would we do the same thing to her here? Of course not. Help her get home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ruth Walker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22244741"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:42:51Z","content":"The government should take better care of its citizens!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Beth Myers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34962034"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:08:30Z","content":"CUBA....has no right to keep her from her son's funeral...the idiots. I would move heaven and earth to be there and hope the Canadian Ambassador fulfills his obligation to get her home NOW!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ann Hewson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/63796587"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:42:45Z","content":"This should never happen to a mother, Never !","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rick Langford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40486513"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:08:22Z","content":"she should at least get to say goodbye to her baby","like_count":0,"author_name":"lorna flunder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66801699"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:52:02Z","content":"This is a mother's worst nightmare.  She needs to be home and bury her son!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Caroline Watkins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78894519"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:05:41Z","content":"The Cdn Embassy needs to step up and do something here. We offer aid to the Cubans and trade with them. And if they are going to be like this close the gates and boycott Cdn visitors to travel to Cuban and vise versa. Obviously they want a payout of some kind.....the bastards.......and the Gov't of Canada needs to step in.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marilyn Rich","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68290532"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:23:03Z","content":"i am a mother, and this is awful. she needs to be able to go to her sons funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"christa link","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1837105"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:41:47Z","content":"SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.  I TOO AM A SINGLE MOTHER AND DONT KNOW WHAT I WOULD DO IN THESE CIRCUMSTANCES. STAY STRONG. MY PRAYERS ARE WITH ALL OF YOU","like_count":0,"author_name":"ESMERALDA ELIZARRARAZ","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78900369"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:58:53Z","content":"Why am I signing this petition. for the simple fact - that it's wrong. Wrong for Cuba to keep Justine Davis... Wrong to not let her come back to Canada and be with her family. There's no rhyme or reason for her to be kept on Cuban soil. \r\nRoxanne","like_count":0,"author_name":"Roxanne Letourneau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66335729"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:29:50Z","content":"She should be able to return home. The accident didn't hurt anyone except her & her son. So why are they holding her? Let her go HOME.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathy Garcia","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78907878"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:36:05Z","content":"I will never go to Cuba, but I think I will sign it ,,for my own reason.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lawence Calcutt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13236466"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:50:26Z","content":"She nees to be able to say goodbye to her child and cope with this tragedy while around a support group of family and friends.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wade Blickenstaff","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78922601"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T15:04:26Z","content":"She needs to lay her son to rest and to feel at peace with this whole tragedy","like_count":0,"author_name":"katrina handsor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13555133"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T15:37:50Z","content":"She needs to come home for her son's funeral","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dominic D'Ornllas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78720101"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:03:22Z","content":"Breaks my heart of humanity to not sympathize with the loss this mother is already feeling......","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stella Iatropoulos","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78724026"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:10:04Z","content":"Friends friend and its sad.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jessica Loxton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78724987"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:29:18Z","content":"Because this mother NEED to be home to lay her son to rest. It is SICKENING that she is being held in Cuba!! I am just beyond disgusted even reading this. Do these people have NO conscience at all? I just hope they remember that \"what goes around, comes around\". ","like_count":0,"author_name":"caitlin winn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24321947"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:09:19Z","content":"There is no reason why this woman whould not be allowed home immediately. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bettina Holman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9610356"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:15:30Z","content":"I am a mother. If this heartbreaking accident happened to me, I would only hope my country wouls assist in getting me home safe to bury my child. A task that is already devastating in itself. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole Wilkinson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43137249"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T19:00:31Z","content":"Tragic Loss, Unimaginable Heartbreak. Bring this woman home, in the name of Humanity and in the name of all Mothers around the world.","like_count":0,"author_name":"nikki horner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78730338"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:30:27Z","content":"I WOULD BE ASHAMED NOT TO HELP & SO SHOULD THE CANADIAN GOVERNMENT","like_count":0,"author_name":"MAERY CALLAGHAN","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68425409"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:14:36Z","content":"best friends niece","like_count":0,"author_name":"louise molloy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78787415"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:20:53Z","content":"compassion","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathy Johnston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72859223"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:56:48Z","content":"Come on guys- sometimes there's more important things than paperwork, and your \"co-ordination\" isn't exactly helping any argument you make in not letting Justine head to the funeral. So just let her head home to the funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Derek Neves","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45096657"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:36:22Z","content":"Because I believe in justice and humanity","like_count":0,"author_name":"Faye Squires","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36922951"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:57:49Z","content":"for obvious reasons","like_count":0,"author_name":"matt quaglino","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78895127"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:13:33Z","content":"The mother needs to mourn and have closure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stuart Coates","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69209941"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:16:18Z","content":"As a mother of a toddler son I feel for Justine.  It's traumatic enough to go through what she has been through!  I don't know Justine but I hope the governments does something to get this woman home to lay her precious boy to rest.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melissa White","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52445586"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:25:39Z","content":"the death of a child is horrible. but not being able to say one last good bye, to see the innocent face one more time, to not be able to give one last kiss or touch before you cant touch there hand again until you  meet in the sky is a devastating feeling. she needs to go home. a child is the light of a mothers soul and to lose that light (child) you die a little inside and feel empty. She deserves to go home before that beautiful boy is 6 ft out of reach physically  and worlds apart spiritually. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"fayleen mason","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78898363"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:28:14Z","content":"This is very issue for all Canadians regarding our government efforts to help them abroad is NOT good enough especially in such a circumstances when they need it.","like_count":0,"author_name":"KALEEM ULLAH MUHAMMAD","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70625503"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:56:32Z","content":"This is the last chance this women has to say goodbye to her SON. It is a tragedy and it is important to her. Anyone would want to be able to attend their CHILD'S funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"JEMMA CIMEUS","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78902723"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:08:13Z","content":"To the embassy in Cuba, \r\n\r\nI should hope that when a Canadian goes abroad, the Canadian government is prepared to leave no stone unturned in order to protect us. You are not there just to make trade deals. Get Justine out of Cuba. Do your job. The job that Canadian taxpayers, like myself, expect you to do. \r\n\r\nDavid Hyatt","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Hyatt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52630739"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:41:58Z","content":"I am a mother, and enjoy my vacations. I can't even fathom trying to give my child an experience that turns tragic, and then not to even be able to lay him to rest. She did not even get to see him to say goodbye. Heartbreaking.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marion Rowe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78909699"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:56:29Z","content":"What's the hold-up all about? Do Canadians take care of their own or not?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Miriam Baer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57051470"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:00:53Z","content":"I read an article on Justices plight this morning. Knowing only some of the circumstances surrounding the story, the Canadian Embassy and the Canadian government in general should be ashamed. I think less and less of our government, our policies and our overall lack of response when it comes to defending and assisting our citizens abroad. Being Cnandian used to mean something. When I see the disgrace, disrespect and disregard award our veterans I am not surprised at the lack of involvement in this issues. For public opinion to change our government needs to start dealing with what really matters. Come on. Canada...step up!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ann Marie Powers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48686396"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:21:03Z","content":"It is apparent that no criminal activities were involved and this injustice is simply the result of some greedy bureaucrat seeking to extort a  bribe before allowing Justine to return to Canada for her son's funeral. Shame of the Canadian officials who have declined to stand up and demand Justine's release, This is just one more in a long list of reasons why I have changed from being a proud Canadian to being ashamed of my country. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ron Craven","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69379261"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:16:08Z","content":"This is beyond heartbreaking and inhumane.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lori Brooks","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10938692"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:32:25Z","content":"Those of us who travel abroad expect Canadian Consular authorities to help us out when we are faced by an emergency. Many of us feel that the Canadian Government does not try hard enough to protect us. Please show that this is not the case by giving Justine the necessary help to return to Canada.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Philip Helwig","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69080403"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:21:24Z","content":"How can a mother not be allowed to be present at her son's funeral?  the Canadian Government must do every thing possible to bring Justine home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Arun Mukherjee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3284226"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:23:14Z","content":"The current government in Ottawa consistently does not do enough to help Canadians in trouble abroad.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nathen Gabriel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32100672"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:33:52Z","content":"This mother needs closure and be able to be at her child's funeral, this is so sad!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cynthia LaBrecque","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13220708"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:50:10Z","content":"How very sad to loose a child. I hope she gets home in time. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Louise Leamen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48454319"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:01:19Z","content":"I work abroad and the assistance from the Canadian government is pitiful  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"james dunlop","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66678316"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:12:29Z","content":"Why would this poor woman be held in Cuba. We provide so much tourism to that country and they should allow her to leave and grieve with her family the loss of her son. Our government needs to put some pressure on the Cuban officials to expedite this situation. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"P Sorrenti","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60116455"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:07:37Z","content":"Because this mother just needs to go home with her family, clearly its an accident! Let her move on...so cruel to make her stay in Cuba!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bridget August","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6201245"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:33:55Z","content":"There is no reason Cuba should still hold her hostage. She needs to be with her son to say goodbye. She's suffered enough.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Estefany Osorio","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31020352"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:23:18Z","content":"She needs to be home and be able to bury her son.  She needs her family","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Gloude","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22424973"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:21:50Z","content":"I'm a mom I would die from a broken heart to not be there to put my child to rest","like_count":0,"author_name":"Abbie Ball","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50511973"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:08:34Z","content":"I dearly hope this can be resolved in time.  I have always advocated against vacationing in Cuba.  Unfortunately many Canadians go annually because it's cheap.  Incidents like this reinforce my position, & underscore that no matter how economical the trip may seem on its face, it's just not worth the possible risks.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katherine Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60746769"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T19:25:34Z","content":"Canada should help get this young woman home - it is the right thing to do.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen Gallagher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76347141"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:53:14Z","content":"Gisele Charland","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gisele Charland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31754036"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:36:31Z","content":"Canadians abroad should expect to be assisted and protected by their government.  Unfortunately, considering the ongoing ineptitude and obscurification practiced by our present PM and the PMO, the lack of information and assistance being offered to Ms Davis can be understood. Canadians deserve better! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Don Bell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11272245"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:47:59Z","content":"She needs to say goodbye to her child. My prayers & condolences to hers & family. Please get her home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Betty Gunn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78782757"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:16:56Z","content":"Justice!!!\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Arlette Boucher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13605381"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:03:18Z","content":"The Canadian government has to do more to help Canadian travelers in distress.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Armstrong","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40728710"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:18:54Z","content":"This mother needs to be there,simple,it is called Humanity.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Didier Marotte",