":"Lucy Sabbatini","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55938866"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:53:21Z","content":"Persons basic right, a mothers divine right in such a loss is to be there. It was an accident and shouldn't be treated and held like a criminal or terrorist.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeanine LaCourse","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16144275"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:14:35Z","content":"Because it is unfair.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Taimi Antigua","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78897149"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:19:40Z","content":"The worse thing a parent could ever go through is bury their son, but if fate has to be that cruel to take away a child, a mother should have every right to be there. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"George Tsonis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78906162"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:24:13Z","content":"Shame on the Canadian Government for not helping a Canadian when they are being unlawfully held in another country. Bring this woman home so she can say goodbye to her child and be with the people who love them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marie Jackson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69300115"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:24:28Z","content":"This is unbelievable! Justine should be allowed to leave Cuba and bury her son. Is she not entitled to a last goodbye?!?!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Ethier - Morgan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51444737"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:33:55Z","content":"Cuba should follow International standards. A traffic fatality is regrettable, but in no way a means to withhold freedom from someone. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emil  Cohen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17310041"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:11:56Z","content":"People do not have no sympathy or love for other anymore?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Yvonne Coleman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46039593"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T19:49:54Z","content":"she deserve to see her child ","like_count":0,"author_name":"valerie lam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78757426"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:14:38Z","content":"My brother Jeffrey was killed in Belize one year ago and the \"Canadian government\" has yet to assist our family find justice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Furgala","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47339972"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:27:33Z","content":"Although it seems unlikely that she can get home by Saturday, I am signing this petition in the hopes that the point can be made that better systems need to be put in place so situations like this do not happen. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Morgan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44241630"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:36:12Z","content":"L'embassade du Canada ne joue pas son r\u00f4le. Repr\u00e9senter et d\u00e9fendre les int\u00e9rets et les droits des ressortissants canadiens \u00e0 l'\u00e9tranger. Surtout \u00e0 Cuba.","like_count":0,"author_name":"walter furlong","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78789325"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:12:27Z","content":"Please let her come home for her son's funeral, she has suffered enough losing him and all her injuries, it would be unbearable not to be at his funeral to say goodbye.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathy Caswell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47335652"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:22:58Z","content":"She should not have more suffering.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sharon Service","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28415128"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:23:08Z","content":"She's a fellow Canadian, and keeping her from her own son would be criminal in my opinion","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michal Drahorat","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73551253"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:35:27Z","content":"I can't imagine the pain of losing a child, but I feel deeply for her. Cuba please let her go.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janice S