ngs happen every day. My son, Alex Eby was detained at Customs at Gatwick Airport in England on December 31st. He was flying to visit his friends. His best friend lives in London, and Alex has visited many times. Both Alex and his friend are training/pursuing careers in soccer/football. The Customs Officer detained him. Locked him up, and he was questioned for about 12 hours.\r\nHis luggage was searched multiple times, and even though he told the complete and absolute truth, they told him that they did not believe him, and that he was being deported. He was held in jail, strip searched and kept with criminals for 3 and a half days while he waited for the next available flight from his carrier at that airport. His passport was seized until he reached Canadian soil. Foreign Affairs Emergency was useless and uninformed. They gave me a number that was never answered and from which calls were never returned. If I had not found an alternate number online I would never have reached my son. I called them back and told them all the misinformation they had given me : phone number, not a jail, no criminals, open access to phone calls and the internet, the ability to have and use his belongings etc. etc. Luckily, there was an end to his issues after a few days. I cannot imagine your family's pain....The Canadian Embassy in London NEVER got around to speaking to my son, even though they had assured me they would, and I had given them his number....just appalling!!!! God bless to these poor people.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daphne Livingston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27494832"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:20:07Z","content":"Have been to Cuba many times. Without action I will simply never go again. This is ridiculous on the part of Cuba and of course shameful on the part of Canada to let it go on. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mike Villeneuve","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14199774"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:42:48Z","content":"I have a son too.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Loretta Murphy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68817568"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:12:06Z","content":"Mother should be able to attend funeral of her Child.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Raphael Abrahms","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16979018"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:19:06Z","content":"A mother DESERVES the RIGHT to lay her child to rest! Although NO parent should bury their child.... Justine Davis MUST do so!!! PLEASE bring her home!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Samantha Annett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78864404"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:48:51Z","content":"because a mother deserves to come home to Canada for her son's funneral. I think it is fucked up that the family has to pay an unreasonable amount to bring back boy's body and it's not fair that the mom cant even go home for her son's funeral.It is heartless that the Cuban governement is doing this and it sucks that the Canadian embassy in CUba isnt make it any easier too.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Josangelica Pinon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78865776"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:24:08Z","content":"Our fellow citizen needs our help!","like_count":0,"author_name":"\u041b\u0435\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0434 \u0411\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39023735"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:18:07Z","content":"this is absolutely gut wrenching.  Elected officials walk a day in the shoes of the family of Justine Davis and do something to help them.  Rest in peace little man.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Heather Finch","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46813490"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:33:10Z","content":"she is a mother in grieve,,and no one should be in a situation like this..the Canadian government needs to support its citizens a 100%..if not so, it is not and does not represent the Canadians then it needs some serious changes ","like_count":0,"author_name":"mehdi zandi","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77652797"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:56:25Z","content":"Justine is a Canadian Citizen.  She is a mother.  She has suffered.  Cuba's actions are inhumane.  No reason to keep this woman away from the funeral of her beloved son.  Canadian citizens need to know we can trust our Government to stand up for us.  We send a lot of tourists to Cuba.  That can all stop if Cuba doesn't agree to release her from an unjust 'captivity'.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marcia Bennett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7680848"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:08:55Z","content":"No intent to commit ? No injuries to the others .. she's suffered enough, and will for the rest of her life ...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Greg Hay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58608853"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:05:06Z","content":"If the lady did no wrong, she deserves to attend her own son's funeral!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lorraine Dalton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32958579"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T23:59:48Z","content":"this mother should be allowed to come home to bury her son","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terri Urbaniak","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37913556"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:21:35Z","content":"She has suffered enough losing her child, allow her to attend his funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sharon Knowlton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40239172"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:04:21Z","content":"I think this is pathetic , they need to let her go home!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Amyotte","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78801629"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:04:19Z","content":"A parent should never have to bury their child...but when they do, they must be there and go through the grieving process with family and friends..such a sad story","like_count":0,"author_name":"cathy fyfe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66270777"},{"created_at":"2014-02-