 Wells","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66677718"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:22:59Z","content":" We are a free country and you are still free to visit a place and return to your own country; dont understand why she just cant get on plane and leave; it was her that lost the most precious thing you could lose, even authorities in a communist country must have children, where is compassion. It wasnt a criminal act on purpose, it was an accident.. How in Gods name can they hold her? Canadian government step in!!! Thats what you are there for, for the people!!!!!\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"SHARON PIERCE","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78875521"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:53:51Z","content":"Being a person who loves to travel, this shocks me that such a well know tourist destination as Cuba would impose such Neanderthal laws on a victim. Until now, I was always wanting to travel to Cuba. Never will I step foot there now.  Not only have the authorities stripped a woman of her rights and freedom, but to be so barbaric as to not let her return to her home and family to mourn the loss of her beautiful boy is beyond understanding.  I hope the Americans are paying close attention here as it seems they may have been on the verge of opening up the possibility of travel to Cuba by reducing some embargo restrictions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"S.V. Kuzma","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65878661"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:25:08Z","content":"I am a mother.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Evelyn Dousett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76021505"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:15:09Z","content":"She should be able to be with her son while he is put to rest.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Passas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78897221"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:27:29Z","content":"Our Canadian government should recognize that their positions are 'strictly' to serve the people and not for their pleasure or profit. Help this woman as you were intended to Mr Ambasador","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ron Burns","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52704577"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:02:49Z","content":"im a mom","like_count":0,"author_name":"danielle la pointe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8418887"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:11:48Z","content":"This could be my little boy some years ago","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joy Sowman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47990811"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:22:38Z","content":"It is a tragedy that no parent should live through... Justin must be home at least to bury her baby","like_count":0,"author_name":"Zarina Hudaybergenova","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78906613"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:43:26Z","content":"The ambassador should do his job.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Arjun Bhatt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62459207"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:08:53Z","content":"So the mother can say final goodbyes to her son","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole Mendez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78914686"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:12:56Z","content":"This is not a criminal case. Why is she being detained?!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Derek Nathaniel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15500444"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:47:38Z","content":"It will be a closure and healing even for Justine that she must be at her son's funeral. And there is no point for Cuban authority to hold her in Cuba.  Careless driving may a a charge, but the lost is her ultimate punishment and pot hole on the street is local authority's problem.\r\nPlease let her go home and put this accident to rest.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Johnny Thanh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78922084"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:40:21Z","content":"it is beyond my comprehension that a governent can prevent this woman from leaving, especially if no one else was injured. I will never go to Cuba is they can do this to people.","like_count":0,"author_name":"linda simpson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75682411"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:06:45Z","content":"It is outrageous that they are keeping her there. I am disappointed and outraged that Canada has not stepped in to help this mother!!! Hitting Facebook to let everyone know not to go to Cuba!!!! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michele Karam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14179503"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:25:09Z","content":"TO WHOM THIS CONCERNS:  I think anyone who has suffered the tragedy of having a child die deserves all the help she/he can get to deal with the tragedy.  It is a simple, humanitarian gesture to allow her to bury her child and will be one of the last, few things she can do for her child.  I believe, also, it will partly enable her to deal with this difficult situation and her grief.  I ask you to give her all the support she needs to come to be at her child's burial.  Thank you, Glenda Miller\r\n\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Glenda Miller","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66478640"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:22:14Z","content":"this is tragic, give her the opportunity to be at the funeral - anything to help the healing and you can help...","like_count":0,"author_name":"susan lillemo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32111297"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:46:12Z","content":"Why not I say...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stew Ray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76229174"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:37:44Z","content":"It's a traffic accident, the other vehicle had no injuries. It's basic human compassion...let her come home and lay rest to her son. Charges (if they need be) can be dealt with after.","like_count":0,"author_name":"April Ruckemann","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78794395"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:29:59Z","content":"it could be me, and I am a mother","like_count":0,"author_name":"karon brown","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/76239583"},