2014-02-06T20:29:53Z","content":"I was planning tour of Cuba next week, but have cancelled my plans...because of this story. Please think of the family, and the effect this will have on tourism in Cuba and free this woman.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Leslie Lewington","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48729694"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:36:18Z","content":"She wants to be a supportive mother and she wants to visit her son's funeral. That is her way of saying goodbye","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nancy Dinh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57539331"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:25:24Z","content":"This is a tragic and sad story on so many levels, especially the loss of a beautiful little boy.  I'm in the travel business and always caution clients to take travel insurance when going to Cuba - and this is a prime reason to do so.  The Cuban government should not be allowing this type of treatment of visitors to their Island.  Even if the doctors don't think that Justine is in any condition to travel, they should give up that responsibility if a Medical Evacuation could be arranged through Justine's insurance company (if she had insurance).  Normally the reason for denial of release is lack of payment, but again I don't know what their reasoning is.  At this point it doesn't really matter, the CDN government should help to have her released from the hospital so that she could come back to attend her son's funeral.  Very sad and a reason that Cuba is not at the top of my list as a recommended place to send clients to.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary De Almeida","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35176455"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:31:21Z","content":"It touched my heart May his soul rest in peace and I pray that his mother is released to say goodbye to her son .","like_count":0,"author_name":"tamara gumbs","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47325985"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T22:16:29Z","content":"It's absolutely horrifying to lose a child 