-02-06T18:24:18Z","content":"If the Cuban police are not laying charges, she should be released.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tina Sutton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52897733"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:35:23Z","content":"Because it could have happened to me r anyone I know.","like_count":0,"author_name":"stacy williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65825603"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:51:40Z","content":"Because i know the island where she went, Cuba should be responsible for the lack of safety on this road, even dangerous when in a taxi!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Guylaine Santerre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78790585"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T06:04:49Z","content":"This is absolutely tragic and she should be able to lay her son to rest. It is hard enough to deal with the passing of a child, but to not be able to be there to lay him to rest, that is just sad! She was clearly a lovin mother and for no reason be held from being able to say goodbye to her son. My ;prayers are with Justine and her family.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tabitha Tangen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74840414"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:59:15Z","content":"This is height of Government insensitivity.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jamal Hyder","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29541195"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:33:23Z","content":"If she has not committed or been charged with a crime, then Cuba needs to leave her alone and let her go home. She lost her son, isn't that enough? ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terri Hailey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6329717"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T12:57:43Z","content":"Fellow mother","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nicole Dauphinais","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78845863"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:37:41Z","content":"Lord, please let this mom get home to say good-bye to her son.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nancy Goyette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52651508"},