gh an agonizing ordeal.She does not deserve to be detained as this was a terrible accident.The Canadian government needs to step up to the plate and get her back home in Canada where she has the support of friends and family .She has suffered a great loss and needs to get home so she can lay her little boy to rest and begin to heal emotionally and physically.Please help her.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jackie Chiasson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48138258"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:30:33Z","content":"Because I can not believe our own Canadian Embassy in Havana and our government are not fighting for our rights. I love Cuba and from being a very frequent visitor, I know they have no rules or respect for Canadian tourists that experience problems abroad and I know exactly the runaround she must be getting. It is shameful and I think the Cuban Tourism Industry should get a taste of their own medicine, perhaps they do not want our tourism anymore, they couldn't make it clearer. I guess 40% of their tourism means nothing to them.  Will have to switch to Dominican Republic or Mexico. Awful shame.","like_count":0,"author_name":"NANCY SMITH","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/69174443"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:32:39Z","content":"I would want to go to my child's funeral too","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dyanna Crowe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78780601"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:34:40Z","content":"She needs to be with her family and mourn the loss of her son at his funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen Chabra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53979094"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:51:33Z","content":"I think the poignancy and urgency of this situation is self-evident and the Canadian government should do something to rectify it NOW.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donna Roode","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74623427"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:28:21Z","content":"It's important for the family.  I can't imagine los