at will send a message since tourism is very important to there economy.  Poor Justine ...to be on her own there in such a tragic time with only strangers to count on. My heart goes out to her and her family.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gina Bauer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78877185"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:53:36Z","content":"Canadians should be able to rely on their government to help them in situations like this.  As a citizen on Canada I expect it.  I support my government believing that those elected realize that they need to, in turn, support us.  My heart goes out to this young woman, let's bring her home.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janice Mckenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50731608"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:07:01Z","content":"For the sake of the mother Justine, who will never find peace if she were not to be there ar rhe funeral of her child. It is just the minimum a mother can ask in life. If she could not enjoy her son alive, let her at least have the consolation of laying him to rest in his tomb. For the sake of humanity, anyone who can do anything for this to happen, please, put yourselves in Justine case and do what you wish others would do for your sake. Thanks. May God bless you and reward you for your efforts","like_count":0,"author_name":"VITTORIO BORIA","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64841585"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:20:20Z","content":"Please let this woman go home TODAY so she has time to make it to her son's funeral.  She has not committed a crime and she is suffering beyond what any parent should.   ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kirsten LaRue","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78897832"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:26:47Z","content":"as a mother my heart crinches she needs to be surround by people who love her","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gixy Rivera","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/51954525"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T14:45:34Z","content":"Sad enough she lost her son....now