d to leave Cuba and travel home to Canada, especially in order to lay her son to rest","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wendy Fielding","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78794324"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:08:24Z","content":"Because I continue to hear stories about the lack of support  Canadians receive  from the Canadian Government when they are involved in these horribly tragic events outside the country. We appear to rush quickly to help other countries\u2026..why don't we help our own? \r\nThis is shameful and we must do a better job. MP's and Mr Harpur\u2026Why is this not a priority?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Dwyer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/53299504"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:26:30Z","content":"It's the decent thing to do!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Orla Lambert-Nickell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13527125"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:29:35Z","content":"I think is just horrible. I mean she is a grieving mother who has lost her child and she is going to have to deal with that for the rest of her life. The Canadian Ambassador's need to get on their job and get this woman home so that she can be there to see her son. I mean have they no sympathy. Why hold her there and no charges? It makes no sense. Send her home!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tiffany Reilly","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48564097"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:59:58Z","content":"If countries such as Cuba accept tourists to visit they have a duty to protect them. This is not the case here. They readily accept that we spend good money to visit.harrasment also applies here.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gaetan Secours","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/67126491"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:56:26Z","content":"This is important to me because I am a mother, and a grandmother, and because I have a heart...please help...this young mother needs to be with her family, and to she needs to be allowed to say good bye to her child. Please have compassion","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Romeril","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43868624"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:06:46Z","content":"The Canadian Government must improve it's protection and care for its citizens needing help out of the country and to act in a more timely manner.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephen Williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32195196"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:12:37Z","content":"putting myself in her shoes...not being able to attend her son's funeral is not something to wish for.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donatien Tshamala","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10281082"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T14:07:14Z","content":"Because she is my sister, my friend, and the 'Auntie Jiji' to my boys. She needs to come home and start the healing process","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amber Hussey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78710467"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T17:22:36Z","content":"I cannot imagine the pain this mother must be feeling.  It is disgusting that this is even an issue..for the love of whatever or whomever you believe in, let this woman come home and say good bye to her precious baby.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Katherine Lin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78735896"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:46:44Z","content":"It is her child. Please allow her to grieve with her family at his funeral. This is heart breaking. She can return to deal with legalities after the funeral. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth Lighthall","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42333442"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:24:46Z","content":"It is the right thing to do! Period.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristin Dennis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78867395"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:15:52Z","content":"I sympathize as a parent and I cannot imagine what she must be going through.  The lack of support from our government is disgraceful as is the total absence of common sense.  I am cer