ered enough\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"angelique gonzalez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58060696"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:55:41Z","content":"A Canadian deserves to come home and attend her son's funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jillene McDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71793630"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T14:50:32Z","content":"Why put more strain on this woman who already has lost so much.","like_count":0,"author_name":"elisa palumbo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78714855"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:49:32Z","content":"Families should be beside their loved ones at their funerals!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lynda Cameron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45645628"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:03:07Z","content":"Common human decency... sad story.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Stephens","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72533255"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:03:01Z","content":"This is a very sad story. Coming from a mother who has lost a child  please let her be home to put her child to rest. Only fair to this broken hearted mother. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charity Machold","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73009381"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:29:02Z","content":"Tracey Mcdonald","like_count":0,"author_name":"tracey mcdonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36414616"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T21:46:57Z","content":"Justine needs to be home for Cameron's funeral!! Canadian Embassy is HEARTLESS!!!!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Thunder Jack","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56198673"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T22:20:25Z","content":"It is this woman's right and for her sanity to be able to bury her son in peace and get some sort of closure on this tragic accident. I don't care who you are... As compassionate human beings who have grieved someone and those who are fellow parents should be able to relate and understand how desperate this woman is to come home... And how she NEEDS to be there for her sons funeral. Bring this poor woman home! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Juliette Tersi","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74975117"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:12:25Z","content":"That is her Son , and No Mother should be not be able to be with him and say her prayers over him and say her hardest Goodbye of her Life ! Canada Give Compassion ! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vanessa McInnis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15728632"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:30:46Z","content":"This is important to me because this lady has been through enough with her father's passing and her young child. She deserves to be able to grieve her son's death at home with her loved ones. Keeping her there is not about doing the right thing because of the law. It's inhumane and about politics in one form or another. Let her go and keep your self-serving nonsense games to yourself. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brenda Reardon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78793011"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:24:57Z","content":"As a Canadian Abroad, I would never want to experience something like this. Please help. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nimet Yusuf","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78803334"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:56:47Z","content":"A mother should definitely be at the funeral of her son.  I am kind of confused as to why she isn't allowed to leave Cuba.  Something isn't right.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wendy Hebert","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/60604838"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:07:18Z","content":"She needs the support of her family. If there are no grounds for investigation, there shouldn't be any reason for her to be held there, especially at a time like this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Madzel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78896223"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:24:34Z","content":"what happen to compassion, sympathy, cry when your neighbor cries or just doing the right thing? she's been through an unimaginable ordeal send her home ","like_count":0,"author_name":"CYNTHIA HILL","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78898239"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:55:44Z","content":"Because there seems to be no reason why she should be detained, and she should be there for her sons funeral. Just another case of Government against citizens.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Roy Sanders","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50288065"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:13:46Z","content":"pour simple raison humanitaire sinon l\u00e9gale  de gr\u00e2ce piti\u00e9 pour cette femme d\u00e9j\u00e0 fortement \u00e9prouv\u00e9e","like_count":0,"author_name":"lise vincent","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56509366"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:49:51Z","content":"If she is a Canadian Ambassador to Cuba and she cannot get assistance, than what would a 'non diplomatic Canadian' expect. More answers are needed! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"KIM WATSON","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40736055"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:24:49Z","content":"This is unnecessary trauma for this poor mother and her family to keep her separated from her family in this time of tragedy. Shame on Cuba for holding her and shame on Canada for not helping their citizen.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Virginia Andersen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78917777"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:08:30Z","content":"This girl needs to be with her family and be there for her son, if it was you or someone you love in this situation, you would want the same thing.  I know I would.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Terri Philpott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70494816"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T17:22:51Z","content":"because it's an injustice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marc Guindon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78735941"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:03:39Z","content":"Burying one's child is the most tragic and painful experience any human being could ever face. Not being present at your child's burial would have long-term and serious psychological effects on the grieving process, which again, will already be intolerably painful. The Cuban government's lack of action on Justine's case is inhumane and entirely unacceptable. If enough people cared, this could turn into an international incident. The entire situation is beyond comprehension and is contrary to common human decency. JUSTINE MUST BE ALLOWED TO COME HOME NOW.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lynda Wood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31624585"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:32:58Z","content":"Canadian embassy employees do little to help Canadians abroad. Justine Davis deserves help.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bill Rankin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52706351"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:29:37Z","content":"cmon now. just let her go cuba :D","like_count":0,"author_name":"nam ton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/72273668"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:03:02Z","content":"It is important to get this mother to her child's funeral. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Amanda Fleming","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34630749"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:15:53Z","content":"As a mother of a son, I would be devastated and consider the Cuban response to be inhumane.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathy Greenlay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66735176"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:22:04Z","content":"She needs closure for loosing her child and needs to be home. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michele Cotnoir","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/75859316"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T21:46:57Z","content":"SHE IS FROM OUR COUNTRY AND IT IS NOT ALWAYS THE WEALTHY WE SHOULD SUPPORT .","like_count":0,"author_name":"KEVIN HURST","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11825590"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:43:54Z","content":"I feel it is horrible that a mother should see her child die in front of her but to be denied saying good bye to him one last time at hi