ight thing to do. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allan Lee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78737345"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:39:25Z","content":"Every Mother deserves to be at her son's funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sierra Lefave","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29737338"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:35:40Z","content":"This could happen to any of us","like_count":0,"author_name":"duane mackenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29674654"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:59:21Z","content":"A friend ","like_count":0,"author_name":"lisa hrynkiw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78750228"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:18:25Z","content":"Lost my entire family when I was 11 years old and was in a coma for 2 weeks. Wasn't able to see any of them before their funeral, so I'm very sympathetic to this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"John Moore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58926579"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:28:18Z","content":"Justice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Monique Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78872943"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:40:22Z","content":"I am also a mother, my heart breaks for her & her family","like_count":0,"author_name":"Emily Wile","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66219682"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:16:22Z","content":"There is nothing to be gained by keeping her in Cuba for either Canada or Cuba.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Thomas Hemeon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/70532780"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:22:36Z","content":"it is a question of humanity - this mother has the right to be home for the funeral of her son","like_count":0,"author_name":"micheline b. ouimet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25385689"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:47:36Z","content":"No mother should ever be refused attendance at her child's funeral, ever.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gillian Adshead","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73037444"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:59:24Z","content":"Krista Shea","like_count":0,"author_name":"Krista Shea","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16978933"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:18:15Z","content":"I will never go to Cuba again!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margaret Rose","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78802798"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:40:51Z","content":"this poor woman should be home with loved ones so she can grieve the loss of her son!! Come on Canada!!! Get her HOME!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Meghann Serrato","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78900198"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:45:30Z","content":"Let this woman bury her child at home.  She has done nothing wrong.  The treatment of this lady is heartless and unacceptable.  Where is the Canadian Government officials?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Diana Hurkens","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34862493"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:18:50Z","content":"No mother should go through this, she deserves closure.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deenah Sallam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/59938096"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:31:03Z","content":"As a frequent traveller to Cuba, I understand the reasons for the procedure required to follow to in turn allow Justine to return home, however as a mother I also understand that perhaps this procedure could be expedited to ensure this mom is allowed to return to Canada for her son's funeral.  She's been through enough so let's bring her home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gail Porter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78590916"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:12:55Z","content":"Mom should be by her sons side","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mike Dhanda","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56812586"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T15:59:19Z","content":"This is as cruel as it can get!","like_count":0,"author_name":"jean michel davignon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64727825"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:10:57Z","content":"Because she should be allowed to be home for the funeral of her child!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Keith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/58934252"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:50:59Z","content":"The Canadian government needs to start doing it's job and looking after it's citizens. Shame on them and yes they do have a bad reputation, in more ways than one. How dare you keep this woman from her child's funeral?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marilyn Glasgow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/195322"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T00:26:49Z","content":"Because it's disgraceful how they are treating her and need to send her home","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ruth Hanratty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78892017"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:24:36Z","content":"This poor woman has already lost her son that is more than one should have deal with.  Please let this women go home to bury her son. Why is she even being held.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pat Barnhill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78898243"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:40:53Z","content":"This is a very clear \"no fault\" accident.  The only thing she did wrong was to deeply love her son.  She needs to be able to go home to where he will be laid in peace and for her  to be close to family and friends so she can have some closure also.  Best wishes Justine...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kimberly Atwater","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78900197"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:43:05Z","content":"This is so sad. Best wishes for your family. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Star Nap","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27667720"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:38:49Z","content":"This is a tragedy, an accident, this poor mom needs to be reunited with her child before his funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bobbi Banks-Morrison","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/57316887"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:22:53Z","content":"Justine should be allowed to get home.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dyane Legg