an officials would recprocate given the conditions were reversed.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ian Ross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47168967"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T03:07:00Z","content":"loosing someone is hard, however when it comes to a mom loosing a child that's even worse. And for the fact that she cannot say goodbye to her child is horrible, and she will always regret it for the rest of her life. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christine Forrester","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48449657"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:00:05Z","content":"Because I am a mother and can't imagine Justine's pain and suffering from the horrible tragedy of her loss.  PLEASE help expedite her return home to mourn with her loved ones!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Gacsady","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78895390"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T05:00:34Z","content":"I urge you to expedite her release until her personal matters are resolved. Its the right thing to do","like_count":0,"author_name":"Yusuf ElRouby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/74753903"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:33:41Z","content":"Embassies are not a vacation resort. They ought to support us, who pay for their salary.and do their job. It is a nonsense what is happening to Justine. We need as a people to support her; she is family and she needs closure wrt her son's death","like_count":0,"author_name":"Claude Emond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54568667"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:41:19Z","content":"An investigation can be done without Justine in  Cuba.  Should she need to be returned, I'm sure that could be arranged with the Canadian Government.  This is critical.  It is her chance for some closure with her son at his funeral.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joann Quigg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/56071850"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:00:56Z","content":"It was an accident and as a mother, I know how hard it would be if I lost my child as is, yet alone not be able to attend the funeral. It's just something that you could never take back. No do-overs. This mom needs to be with her close family and friends so that she could grieve, have family support and have some closure. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary Mertens","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78903375"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:17:20Z","content":"Je crois que c'est un droit humain fondamental que de donner l'opportunit\u00e9 \u00e0 une m\u00e8re que d'assiter aux fun\u00e9railles de son fils.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andr\u00e9 Tremblay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21842039"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:41:51Z","content":"I can only imagine how the poor mother of the little boy feels.  She will be heart broken.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marjorie Rapson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73236720"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:52:06Z","content":"With all the tourist dollars spent by Canadians in cuba there shouldn't be any nonsense in regards to ANY Canadian.  Canadians are the ones who have propped up Cuban economy for many, many years.\r\nstop the nonsense","like_count":0,"author_name":"ed knight","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45787017"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T15:59:41Z","content":"This is cruel!  This woman's life is changed for ever.  She has lost her son and now cannot say good bye to him.  Let her come to the funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maria Neves","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78723445"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:19:14Z","content":"Please get her home so she can be there when her little angel is laid to rest.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cora Langcaster","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78726356"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:39:23Z","content":"let this boy come home to have his last days with the ones that love him...Justine needs his family ..god bless you","like_count":0,"author_name":"belinda crack","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/73304998"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:14:47Z","content":"She's a Canadian citizen in a difficult situation. Our government should do all it can to help one of its own. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jesse McLean","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/77671495"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:58:20Z","content":"Being Cuban myself living in Canada, I understand that the separation from one's family can cause distress and emotional harshness. The last moments a mother can share with her late 3 year old son is a sacred bond and it shouldn't be affected by the politics of a country.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dany Vergara","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/71315851"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:05:21Z","content":"Freedom???? Where????","like_count":0,"author_name":"Douglas VanLuttervelt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68389302"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T00:25:54Z","content":"mother should be at sons funeral","like_count":0,"author_name":"vanessa gaudet","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78788410"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:33:42Z","content":"feelings of humanity,as we are all children/decendents of Adam & Eve thus related & as per teachings of Islam we should stand by each other during time of need/feel for each other if a calamity befalls on anyone of us  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"SHAHID AHMED","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66677055"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:31:31Z","content":"On humanitarian grounds.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mohammed Niaz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65967086"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:50:30Z","content":"George pouliot\r\n\r\nGeorge Pouliot","like_count":0,"author_name":"george pouliot","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78911216"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:15:27Z","content":"Wshing happiness and resolve somehow in this tragedy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tina pery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54652060"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T12:19:38Z","content":"As Canadians we must do everything in our power to get Justine home to bury her son Cameron","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marian Ricalis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78841671"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:11:13Z","content":"Every parent needs to be there for their child in life and in death!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kim Creed","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14716728"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:24:35Z","content":"I am a mother of two young kids and love to travel with my family - the thought of this happening to another mother is too tragic for words...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Matthews","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9374528"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T17:26:29Z","content":"I could not imagine losing a child, let alone not having the closure of the funeral and being able to say goodbye... If it were me I would NEED this in order to be able to go on with life. Bring this poor broken hearted mother home!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Aimee Schott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78736509"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:50:36Z","content":"As a mother myself. And losing a child. I know how this mother must be feeling. Cuba let her go. Have some compassion. You have no right detaininbf her fromher own sons funeral. How sad this world is when tragedies like this happen. My prayers and heart go out to you.....","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dianne Pothier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30327370"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:30:36Z","content":"Our Government needs to better support Canadians who are trapped in such horrible circumstances. this Mother deserves a chance to have closure with her sweet boy.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Beth Feor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/52758864"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:51:25Z","content":"She should be allowed to leave until the Cuban officials finish their investigations","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maria Kenyon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24305036"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T17:27:05Z","content":"it's hard enough to lose a child, it shouldn't be this hard to attend the funeral. no matter what country you are in there is a universal understanding among humans that this should be a no-brainer","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lesley Pacheco","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/64074168"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:05:23Z","content":"fuckin important ","like_count":0,"author_name":"emeth whatmough","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25563750"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:16:54Z","content":"01294272765","like_count":0,"author_name":"june mclaughlin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27420911"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:37:43Z","content":"A mother deserves to say good bye to her child is first and foremost, but to be detained because she was involved in an accident that almost killed her is outrageous. She is Canadian and should be allowed to come home. She broke no law!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lynda Arthur","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28019375"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:59:19Z","content":"A tragic injustice","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine Gross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66712887"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T02:06:23Z","content":"This is an outrage, no family member should be held back from attending a funeral, especially a Mother going to her 3yr old Sons funeral.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandy Diamond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/65835003"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:15:47Z","content":"This was a tragic accident and to put a mother through the pain of not only loosing her child but not being able to go home is inhuman. The mother needs to grieve and have the support from friends and family at this time and for many years to come. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Chesney","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78897274"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T01:27:50Z","content":"I am a mother to 3 sons.  To have this happen at all is a terrible tragedy.  It is unacceptable (to put it mildly) for this to happen or to have it continue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Crystal von Hugo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30162128"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:12:06Z","content":"This mo had been through enough and she needs to come home!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristen Duncan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48081558"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:16:28Z","content":"The Cuban Government is a Communist dictatorship.  It is not Canada's friend. It is unfortunate that it takes events like this to remind us. The Canadian Government must forget political correctness and do the right thing. TELL, don't ASK the Cuban Government that Justine is coming home for her son's funeral. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"James  Williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13162425"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:25:13Z","content":"I am a mother","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margarita LOZANO","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/55497972"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:52:43Z","content":"SHE HAS THE WRIGHT TO BURRY HER SON JUST LIKE YOU WOULD\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Suzanne Charlebois","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20636488"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:47:57Z","content":"On January 18th ,on the A.C. flight to Havana,my wife sat next to Justine's sister. We were shocked to read the petition and hear how uncooperative the Can. government has been. What a sad story! We offer our condolences and best wishes for Justine's recovery and return to Canada","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Evans","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28336465"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T16:32:49Z","content":"heartbreaking story","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cynthia Stevens","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78728305"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:10:30Z","content":"This is devastating. As a mother of 4 year old and a 1 1/2 year old I can not imagine the heartbreak of this poor woman. Losing a child is every parents worst nightmare. How can she not be allowed to come home? This is ridiculous","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dawn O'Brien","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78743189"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:14:37Z","content":"It would be unimaginable to miss your child's funeral because of something so crazy.  It has been stated by the Cuban police that there was no mal-intent, why is she still being detained?  She should have the support of our Canadian government to ensure a safe trip home to attend her sons farewell.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kylie Winterstein","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78864193"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T18:24:34Z","content":"No Canadian should suffer in another Country without the aid of our Government officials.  I would feel abandoned and alone if it were me.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shelley Bark","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/67298322"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:38:51Z","content":"Justine deserves too be at the funeral for her child. The Canadian Government should help bring her home too be with her family. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brenda Edwards","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78794485"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T01:59:11Z","content":"A mother should be there for her child's funeral. It's horrific enough to lose a child but to not be able to have the opportunity to say goodbye is terrible. Other arrangements should be able to be made to please all the officials and allow her to come home. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Coral Deacon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32491834"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T02:53:49Z","content":"Support","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michael Collins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78800769"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T02:25:14Z","content":"retired","like_count":0,"author_name":"jeff payne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/68238839"},{"created_at":"2014-02-07T03:17:21Z","content":"That could be any of us","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laura Dunn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62057666"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T14:04:41Z","content":"she did nothing wrong and deserves to be at her son's funeral!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donna Babcock","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16670884"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:33:41Z","content":"this mother needs closure! being physically present for his funeral! Plus! maybe helmets need a double look for safety!!! or was all of this some HORRIBLE SERIES OF  FLUKE?!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nancy Bragg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/nancybragg"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T16:29:56Z","content":"This lady has done nothing wrong! Regardless, she NEEDS to be home for her sons funeral! Let her go home","like_count":0,"author_name":"N Thorne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50284828"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T20:00:00Z","content":"Please let this woman come home. This is ridiculous that a person is held in a foreign country. We love to visit the islands but every time you hear a story like this it makes you think twice. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"cheryl Valnion","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78758719"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:07:24Z","content":"Because citizens rights and freedoms are being trampled on in this country. All of a sudden it's shameful to be Canadian because of how corrupt and content our politicians are. It would be great if the people I pay to do a job actually did their job.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rob Caldwell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78877564"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:14:02Z","content":"It breaks my heart that she cannot be there to bury her own son.  Shame on YOU!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mary-Anne Appleby","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/78877872"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:52:45Z","content":"This is a terrible accident and this mother should not be denied coming home for her sons funeral.  She has been through enough.  Bring her home ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sue Yach","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38660828"},