d before Christmas and she is able to travel she should definitely be helped to come home for her son's funeral. Not to be there could interfere with her ablility to work through her grief. \r\n\r\nSurely there must be some way to ensure that she goes back if Cuba really needs her for an investigation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gail Golding","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36667059"},{"created_at":"2014-02-05T18:53:25Z","content":"Unanswered pleas for the condition of her daughter left unheard,  only to find out she had died at the scene? Not allowing her to leave the country to even put her own daughter to rest? I think that speaks for itself ...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Christopher J. Weintz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/54753345"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T19:53:03Z","content":"This her child it's only right that she's there for him and also this is where she lives. Set her free.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bonnie Lecky","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46948707"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T20:49:01Z","content":"Compassion","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rita Patenaude","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/66901943"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:07:25Z","content":"Omg, she should definitely be entitled to be with her family.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michael Kulmatycki","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15373081"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:20:24Z","content":"It is not right that she should miss her son's funeral. Losing a child is devastating enough.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chelsea Assoignon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36046475"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T21:32:05Z","content":"A mother's grief is enough for me to sign this petition.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jeffrey Collicott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3617296"},{"created_at":"2014-02-06T23:40:50Z","content":"As a mother and a Canadian I could not imagine going through this.  I am disappointed in the Canadian government.","like_count"